{
  "stem": "945.1",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "That was just the-- the first year, grade one, grade two.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "It was a public school.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But I think there were only six grades, if I'm not mistaken.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "It's a long time ago.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 5 SECONDS] Having had to walk to school every day and back from school, and I was just a little boy-- six, seven years old-- I will never forget the fear that I had in walking that short distance.",
      "word_count": 41
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Because we were only two or three Jewish families surrounded by mostly Ruthenian, Ukrainian people which did not appreciate us in their midst.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "To me, they not only called me names, but they also threw rocks at me and at many times threatened me with their dogs.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "So the walk to school and back was a very painful experience.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Which, at that time, I couldn't understand why.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "But now that I look back, I realize that it was the first demonstration of, if you may call it, anti-Semitism, or hatred towards Jews.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "My grandfather [INAUDIBLE] Leib, my mother's father, was a great [INAUDIBLE] of the Vishnitz Rabbi.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And he disregarded the surroundings he lived in and dressed himself in the traditional Hasidic garb.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And-- [CRYING]",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "[DRINKS] --and walked every Saturday [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] to Vishnitz to attend Shabbos prayers.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] And, on many occasions, I went along with him, just a little boy.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And those are memories which will always be with me.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So both my grandparents left me with very fond memories.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "On the one side, the traditional, orthodox life and thinking and being.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And my other grandfather, which wasn't a great orthodox-- it wasn't extremely religious, but the-- a more modern type of believing and being a Jew in a more modern way.",
      "word_count": 30
    }
  ],
